["0/united states/", "1/united states/north carolina/", "2/united states/north carolina/ashe/", "3/united states/north carolina/ashe/west jefferson/"], "contributor": ["university of north carolina at chapel hill library, chapel hill, nc"], "date": "1937-12-09", "dates": ["1937-12-09"], "description": ["THURSDAY DECEMBER IM Upturn In Business In 3B Is Predicted By Leading Bankers Roger Babson Also Thinks Pre sent Recession Blessing In Disguise The current slump in business throughout the nation will not re sult in another depression the up turn will come in 1938 leading bankers in the country and Roger W Babson declared last Sunday The concensus of opinion among 125 bank presidents and executives of the most important banks in 44 states having a total deposits of twelve billion dollars is that the present business recession will run its course for four more months or more bhit the upturn will then come In his regular forecast column Sunday Mr Babson declared that in his opinion the present slump is a blessing in disguise He thinks that the country is just passing through a readjustment period Lewis said the replies indicated bankers believe an upturn in busi ness is dependent upon a demon strated change in attitude on the part of the administration toward business Ranking first among recovery measures suggested Lewis said was repeat of the undistributed earnings tax next balancing of the budget third lowering of taxes on capital gains fourth increase in rail freight rates"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-12T17:37:57.977Z", "group": ["ndnp/ncu", "university-of-north-carolina-chapel-hill-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92073203/1937-12-09/ed-2/?sp=5", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02:data:sn92073203:00332893014:1937120902:0615/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=287&w=196", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_laga